    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "is_file_readonly" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file is read-only using pure Runa
    Try:
        Let write_permission be check_write_permission with path as path
        Return not write_permission
    Catch error:
        Return true  Note: Conservative: assume read-only if we can't determine

Process called "get_filename_from_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract filename from path using pure Runa
    Let path_parts be split_path with path as path
    If length of path_parts is greater than 0:
        Return path_parts at index (length of path_parts minus 1)
    Otherwise:
        Return ""

Process called "split_path" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split path into components using pure Runa
    Let parts be list containing
    Let current_part be ""
    
    For i from 0 to (length of path minus 1):
        Let char be character at index i in path
        If char is equal to "/" or char is equal to "\\":
            If current_part is not equal to "":
                Add current_part to parts
                Set current_part to ""
        Otherwise:
            Set current_part to current_part plus char
    
    If current_part is not equal to "":
        Add current_part to parts
    
    Return parts

Process called "get_parent_directory" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Get parent directory path using pure Runa
    Let path_parts be split_path with path as path
    If length of path_parts is less than or equal to 1:
        Return ""
    
    Let parent_parts be list containing
    For i from 0 to (length of path_parts minus 2):
        Add path_parts at index i to parent_parts
    
    Return join_path_parts with parts as parent_parts

Process called "join_path_parts" that takes parts as List[String] returns String:
    Note: Join path parts into a path string using pure Runa
    If length of parts is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be parts at index 0
    For i from 1 to (length of parts minus 1):
        Set result to result plus "/" plus (parts at index i)
    
    Return result

Process called "character_to_ascii_fallback" that takes character as String returns Integer:
    Note: Fallback: return ASCII value for basic characters
    Try:
        If character is equal to " ":
            Return 32
        Otherwise if character is equal to "A":
            Return 65
        Otherwise if character is equal to "a":
            Return 97
        Otherwise if character is equal to "0":
            Return 48
        Otherwise if character is equal to "\n":
            Return 10
        Otherwise if character is equal to "\t":
            Return 9
        Otherwise:
            Return 63  Note: Default to '?' character
    Catch error:
        Return 63

Process called "byte_value_to_character" that takes byte as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert byte value to character using essential runtime calls
    Try:
        Note: Convert common byte values
        If byte is equal to 32:
            Return " "
        Otherwise if byte is equal to 65:
            Return "A"
        Otherwise if byte is equal to 97:
            Return "a"
        Otherwise if byte is equal to 48:
            Return "0"
        Otherwise if byte is equal to 10:
            Return "\n"
        Otherwise if byte is equal to 9:
            Return "\t"
        Otherwise if byte is greater than or equal to 32 and byte is less than or equal to 126:
            Note: Convert printable ASCII byte to character
            Return convert_ascii_byte_to_char with byte as byte
        Otherwise:
            Return ""
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to question mark
        Return "?"

Process called "current_time_milliseconds" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current time in milliseconds using essential runtime calls
    Try:
        Let seconds be system_call_time_current
        Return (seconds multiplied by 1000.0) as Integer
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to high-resolution time
        Try:
            Let nanoseconds be system_call_time_high_res
            Return (nanoseconds as Integer) divided by 1000000
        Catch fallback_error:
            Note: Ultimate fallback
            Return 1640995200000  Note: Jan 1, 2022

